{
  "stem": "8786.4",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Malthausen was already those days-- there was no work there was nothing to do.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "This was just a death camp waiting for the-- they were waiting that everybody should close his eyes.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We were there for about three weeks.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And then we were given an order to go further, which was already the-- towards Gunskirchen.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "We didn't know what will wait for us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "But it was a horrible three days of marching from Malthausen to Gunskirchen.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Gunskirchen is in a forest.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "But the horrible thing about it was that we did not have the strength to go.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "No food, no water.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "One night, I think they were saying that the Germans were planning to bomb us.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] They didn't know what to do with us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "So there was question that they should take German planes and bomb us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "We were in a mine field.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And this march was three days without food.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And those guards of ours, they were just looking for the weak people.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "Anybody who couldn't walk was taken aside and killed.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "This is when my friend, Lax Dini, was begging us, please pick me up.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "Please pick me up because I don't have the strength to go.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And I've seen these two brothers and a child-- a father and a son, and the father's brother, an uncle.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "Also the same thing.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "They picked up these boys on the stretcher and they were walking with him.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "I don't know how long did they go.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "I had another friend of mine who did not continue to go because his father couldn't go.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "Deutsch Tapsi was his name.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "Deutsch [INAUDIBLE], Uncle Edush, was the father.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "And his son just did not want to leave the father.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
